.row
	
	.col-md-6
		p The Facebook ID will be used to authenticate and offer the athlete the ability to update their profile.
		p To find their ID, copy the athlete's Facebook URL and paste in the following page:&nbsp;
			strong
				a.btn.btn-facebook.btn-xs.btn-wd.btn-fill(href="http://findmyfbid.com/", target="blank") Search FB ID
		p
			small.text-info If you get an error, we will have to manually authenticate this user for their account when they request to claim.
	.col-md-6
		p The Instagram ID will be used to try to pull images from 
			span(ng-bind="athlete.profile.firstName || 'the athlete'")
			|'s instagram account.
		p To find their Instagram ID, type in their instagram username in teh following page:&nbsp;
			strong 
				a.btn.btn-facebook.btn-xs.btn-wd.btn-fill(href="https://smashballoon.com/instagram-feed/find-instagram-user-id/", target="blank") Search Instagram ID
		p
			small.text-info If you get an error, this athlete will have to manually add their instagram account once they've claimed this profile.
.row
	.col-md-6
		.form-group
			label 
				i.fa.fa-lock
				|&nbsp;&nbsp; Facebook ID
			input.form-control(name="fbID", ng-model="athlete.fbId")
	.col-md-6
		.form-group
			label
				i.fa.fa-lock
				|&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter Instagram ID
			input.form-control(name="igID", ng-model="athlete.igId")
hr
.row
	.col-md-12
		h6.title Public Contact Information
		button.btn.btn-xs.btn-fill.btn-default.pull-right Add Account
.row
	.col-md-6(ng-repeat="account in athlete.social")
		.form-group
			label {{ account.service}}
			input.form-control(ng-model="account.link")
	